      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISTER AMERICANO (1) comes through the Gold Chalice series at Bathurst, where he was fourth in his heat then held up when beaten 3.6 metres in a consolation. Suited dropping in grade and was fourth at Listed level the last time he drew on the pegs so is likely to get the favours. ZANDA MAN (4) put together a series of wins over a similar distance to this earlier in his campaign and could be close to another success after a strong performance to go under by a nose in the Blue Lake Classic last start at Mt Gambier. INTRUSION (8) scored back-to-back wins before coming from this barrier and working but fighting well to go under by just a neck at his most recent appearance at this venue. NEATNTIDY (2) drew poorly and worked last start but had looked close to a win with a string of placings prior, missing by a nose here two back. Draws much better so can bounce back.",
